President Obama expresses his disappointment in the Senate's failure to confirm Debo Adegbile as the leader of the Civil Rights Division at the Department of Justice. He believes that Adegbile is a highly qualified and deserving candidate, with impeccable qualifications and a strong dedication to protecting civil and Constitutional rights. Obama also highlights Adegbile's personal story of overcoming adversity and becoming a respected litigator. He criticizes the Senate's decision, stating that it goes against the fundamental principle of justice and denies the American people an outstanding public servant.